@baseUrl = http://localhost:5169

### 1. Get All Skills
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/skills


### 2. Create a new Skill
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/skills
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Comfortable with Linux CLI",
  "description": "Learn basic bash commands, file navigation, and permissions.",
  "status": 0
}

### 3. Create Another Skill
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/skills
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Git Fundamentals",
  "description": "Master git clone, commit, push, pull, and branching.",
  "status": 0
}


### 4. Add Prerequisite (Skill 2 requires Skill 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/skills/2/prerequisites
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "id": 1
}


### 5. Check if Skill 1 can be started
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/skills/canStart/1


### 6. Check if Skill 2 can be started (should be locked)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/skills/canStart/2


### 7. Get Skill Logs
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/skills/1/logs


### 8. Add a Skill Log
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/skills/1/logs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "note": "Completed the Linux file system navigation section.",
  "amount": 45
}

### 9. Get Unlocked Skills
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/skills/unlocked

### 10. Get Completed Skills
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/skills/completed

### 11. Get Recommended Skills (Top Priorities)
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/skills/recommended